    "## 1. My lane (or freestyle) and why\n",
    "\n",
    "**Provisional lane: Lane 1 — Ranking Signal Analysis.**\n",
    "\n",
    "Lanes 2 and 4 already assume the shape of the decision (a ranked refresh queue, a CTR-gap\n",
    "score). Before I commit to building a specific scoring model, I want to answer a more basic\n",
    "question first: which signals in this data actually carry real information about content\n",
    "performance and movement, and which ones just *sound* like they should matter?\n",
    "\n",
    "The quick check in Section 3 below is why this lane earns its 7 weeks. A naive first pass says\n",
    "\"nothing here is linearly related to movement\" — every continuous signal I checked (position,\n",
    "CTR, word count, age, freshness, engagement rate) has a near-zero correlation with `trend_pct`.\n",
    "If I stopped there, I'd conclude the data has no signal. But grouping by `content_type` instead\n",
    "of treating it as one blob shows a real, sizeable difference in decline rates between content\n",
    "types. That contrast — flat when you look for a straight line, real when you look for structure\n",
    "— is exactly the kind of finding a signal audit exists to catch, and it's the evidence base I'd\n",
    "want in hand before deciding whether (and how) to build a Lane 2/4-style scoring model in later\n",
    "weeks."
   ]
  },
