   "source": [
    "## 2. The question: decision, action, cost of a wrong call\n",
    "\n",
    "**Unit of analysis:** one row = one content item (a page), identified by `content_id`, scoped to\n",
    "one client (`client_id`), measured over a fixed trailing 90-day window. Not a client, not a day —\n",
    "a page-level snapshot.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research question:** Across FlyRank's content inventory, which observable signals — search\n",
    "position, CTR, freshness, content age, content type, engagement — show a real, meaningful\n",
    "association with content performance and movement, and which commonly-assumed signals turn out\n",
    "to be weak or misleading on their own?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Decision this improves:** Before FlyRank spends review capacity or model-building effort\n",
    "chasing any one signal (\"watch freshness,\" \"watch CTR\"), which signals actually carry real\n",
    "information — so limited attention goes to signals that matter and skips ones that only look\n",
    "meaningful.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Who acts, and how:** A content strategist or SEO lead deciding which few metrics to check first\n",
    "when triaging hundreds of pages with limited review time. Downstream, whoever builds a scoring or\n",
    "ranking model in later weeks (Lane 2/4-style work) uses this audit to decide which features are\n",
    "worth engineering in and which are noise.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cost of a wrong call:** If I report a signal as meaningful when it's actually noise (e.g.\n",
    "\"word count predicts decline,\" when the observed correlation is about -0.01), the team spends\n",
    "scarce review hours filtering pages by a signal that doesn't generalize — while a content type\n",
    "that actually declines at roughly twice the rate of another keeps getting the same review\n",
    "priority as everything else. Run the error the other way — dismiss `content_type` because the\n",
    "single-variable correlations look flat overall — and the team misses a real, actionable pattern.\n",
    "Either mistake wastes limited editor hours on the wrong pages."
   ]
  },
